spanGrp.span: hąąke Hoocąk hoitʼera xawanį hii hiiranįgi pįįną yaare waaʔųaje
I think it would be good if they don't lose the Hoocąk language
(hąke) Hocąk hoit'era xawanįhi hiranį gipįną yaare wa'ųąje
hagairašge woceexinįįsge nųnįge hegų žige žige hajiikere
sometimes it's hard, but then I get going
hagairašge woocexinįsge nųnįge hegu žige žige hajikere
that's why it's good what they're doing, I think
stoo kįiranąga tee haraire Hoocąk hitʼera wagigųs nąąʔįnąąkre
they get together and carry on teaching the Hoocąk language
stokįnąnąga tee haraire Hocąk hit'era wagigųs ną'įnąągre
peežega roogųiregi nųnįge hotažiške jaagu hišge šʔaak wahiire rašąną Hoocąk hitʼera šąną airešųnų eeja
whoever wants to... their parents only used to speak Hoocąk
peežega roogųįnegi nųnįge hotažiške jaagu hišge š'aak wahiire rašąną Hocąk hit'era šąną 'airešųnų
"'eeja" missing at the end? -- LP: Yes, added on tx.
xete howahiire taa waʔųną eesge ke wažą hiraire
when they grow up, they don't care
xete wawahiire ta wa'ųną 'eesge ke waža hiraira
teeži jaagu watapį hajegają hąąke žeesge eeja howatanįšge
I can talk and understand it, even if I don't go over there
teeži jaagu watapįį hajegają hąke žeesge 'eeja wawatanįšge
waaca eesge nųnįge hota hąąke wawagigųsiranį
I see that even then some didn't teach them
waaca 'eesge nųnįge hota hąke wawagigųs hiranį
ee saagre anąga eegiige ee wažąraįžą ee roogųire
it's faster, whatever they want to say
ee wažąraįžą ee roogųire guąnegų saagre aire
whatever they want to say, they say it straight away, they say it faster
jaagu hąąpteʔe wažą hanąąc saagranąk eesge hegų žeʔe xapgegi xapge
today everything (society) is faster, that's why it's quicker
jaagu hąąpte'e wažą hanąąc saagranąk 'eesge hegu že'e xapgegi xaapge
they get it over with they get going
hokišipre hire anąga hegu žige hajiakaraire
really "žige"? -- LP: Not clear, audio quality is very bad.
eesge hegųregi roohąxjį wąąkšik wacekra hąąke hoitʼetʼera warapį hiiranį waʔųnąąk
a lot of the young people they don't know the language
'eesge hegunegi roohąxjį wąąkšik wacekgra hąke h(o)it'et'era warapį hiranį wa'ųnąąk
hegųňegi is it warapį hire or warapįire??
nųnįge hįwawašakwigiži hagoreižą waruxįknįįsge hikisgairegają heesge hiinąąkšąną
if we do it, sometime, there'll be a kind of wake up feeling, that's what they're doing
nųnįge hiwawašak wigiži hagoreižą waruxįgnįsge hikisgaire gają heesge hiinąąkšąną
I tell them that, those I can reach I tell them that
hoitʼera hįkaraigąšwigi hąąke gipįkjene yaagige hisge hiranąʔįire
it's not going to be funny if we lose our language, I tell them and they belive it
hoit'era hįkaraigašwigi hąke gipįkjane yagigi sgeraną'įne
heesge hegų hahuireanąga hiperes roogųire žee aire waʔųnąąk
that's why they come to me, they say they want to learn
heesge hegu hahuireanąga hiperes roogųįne že 'aire wa'ųnąąk
eegi hąąke hižą roogųnįge hąąke hawe wahaanį
if someone doesn't want to I don't bother them
hąąke ee hirairanąga hiperes roogųiregi jaagu waagijiteną
if they wanted to learn, I could help them
hąke 'ee hirairanąga hiperes roogųįegi jaagu wagijiteną
eesge nųnįge žige hirakisanįk eeja wąąkšik wacek hinųk hota wawaakitʼe hajawi
on the other hand, we talk to some of the young girls
'eesge nųnįge žige hirakisaanįk 'eeja wąąkšik wacek hinųk hota wawakit'e hajawi
wažąrą roohąxjį eeja hinųkįk nąąkre woikigųs jaasge hįgigųsirawira
there are a lot of things for these young girls, the teaching, how they taught us
wažąną roohąxjį 'eeja hinųgįk nąągre wogigus jaasge hįgigushirawira
they've got the chance they gave us
hišge wawaagitakwigi wagijire wagijire wawagiʔų hajawi
when we tell them this, we are helping them
hišge wawagitakwigi wogijire wogijire wawagi'ų hajawi
woicątʼįra heesge hiiną higicgairegają pįįže hiraire
we're pointing out what they try to do, they think it's good
woicąt'įną heesge hiiną higicgaire gają pįįže hiraire
that's why they started doing that
nųnįge guirešge hota watuugaširehawira keenį wawaakitʼawinįšge hąąke pįįnį hiirenąąk
even then, it was too late for some of them, before we got to talk to them, they weren't doing good
nųnįge guirešge hota watugažire hawira kenį wawakit'awinįšge hąke pįįnį hiirenąąk
they had already done something wrong
hąąke jaasge eegi haawianąga haakja žige žee ceek hajiakaraireanąga hąąke heesge hoʔųpįįnį
if they get into something, whatever we do, we can't get them back and they can't start over
hąke jaasge 'eegi hawianąga haakja žige žee ceek hajiakaraireanąga hąke heesge ho'ųpįįnį
heesge nųnįge hota (ke) keenį wooʔehi hokitʼųreiranį heepeja wawaagitakwigi aire
they say some of them had already gotten into something, before we could tell them
heesge nųnįge hota ke kenį wo'ehi hokit'ųnąįranį heebeja wawagitakwigi 'aire
check whether hokit'ųre can alos mean sth. like "get in with" (law/court)!
heesge žige žige žee heesge haahajawi eesge wagijire roohąxjį hagijitawigįnį
that's what we do, we've already helped quite a few of them
heesge žige žige žee heesge hahajawi 'eesge wogijire roohąxjį hagijitawiginį
I cannot tell any names (implying: they're confidential)
